HEADWORD: Moppet
<hw>Mop"pet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From 3d
<er>Mop</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A rag baby; a puppet made of
cloth; hence, also, in fondness, a little girl, or a woman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A long-haired pet dog.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mopsy</ent>⟦br⟧
